            <title>[DATAMONGO-647] Using &quot;OrderBy&quot; in &quot;query by method name&quot; ignores the @Field annotation for field alias.</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-647</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I created a method using the &quot;query by method name&quot; approach:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Inside my Answer object, I have a field called &quot;Score&quot; that is annotated with&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Field(&quot;sr&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
int Score&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;List&amp;lt;Answer&amp;gt; findByQuestionIdOrderByScoreDesc(String questionId)&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;When the query is run, the database attempts to sort the results by &quot;score&quot; rather than my &quot;sr&quot; field name.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
